review_blob: Excellant. I have a had multiple years of this beer all are very good. The flavors change as it ages. 08 was I felt the best very balanced and smooth. 09 was very light and smooth as well.  10 and 11 are both very good but will benefit from a couple years in the cellar.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Hands down the best beer I have ever had. Period end of review. Oh well just for fun, the aroma is incredible two years of sitting in a bourbon barrel will do that.  The appearence is pitch black darkness.  The taste is money huge bourbon lots of sweetness. For how boozy it smells it is incredibly smooth. Overall as I said the best beer I have ever had.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Rare

review_blob: The aroma is very strong.  Lots of bourbon and alcohol in the aroma.  The appearance is like used motor oil.  Just pitch black.  The taste is very sweet and a very strong bourbon flavor.  There is a little burn from the alcohol but that mellows as it ages. The palate is the best part of this beer.  It is a very thick stout. Overall BCS is outstanding. One of the best beers there is.

Very big ipa. the aroma was not there for me not anything very strong.  The taste is very sweet not much hop flavor.  I prefer a more hop forward ipa.  there is a little bit of an alcohol burn but not much. Overall it is another great brew from Dogfish head.

very citrus and hop forward aroma. Deep caramel color with a light thin head.  The taste is hoppy and citrus.  You get the bitterness of the hops at the finish. Overall a very solid beer great for when you feel like enjoying one of 3Fs many great brews.
